Clean Fix (Since This Is Dev) - When there is some issue in database and you want to start from clean slate.

-Drop DB
-Regenerate migration
-Apply fresh schema


🔥 Step 1 — Drop Everything
docker-compose down -v

🔥 Step 2 — Delete Alembic Versions
backend/alembic/versions/*

🔥 Step 3 — Make Sure User Model Uses UUID (this was required when there was an issue on the UUID vs Integer mismatch)
edit backend/app/models/user.py
Ensure it inherits from UUIDMixin: class User(UUIDMixin, TimestampMixin, Base):
And there is no Integer id anywhere.

Search your entire project: grep -R "Integer, primary_key" , It should return nothing.

🔥 Step 4 — Remove create_all()
Base.metadata.create_all(bind=engine)
We are 100% Alembic-driven now. So we don't need any hard-binding in main.py

🔥 Step 5 — Start DB Fresh
docker-compose up -d

🔥 Step 6 — Generate Migration Again (From backend (venv active):)
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "initial uuid schema"

🔥 Step 7 — Apply Migration
alembic upgrade head


